Sentencas: A 3D integrated numerical model is constructed to evaluate the thermal-fluid behavior and thermal stress characteristics of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Thermal stress and thermo-electrochemical analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell: Effects of anode porosity

Sentencas: Effects of anode porosity on performance, temperature gradient and thermal stress are investigated.
Titulo: Thermal stress and thermo-electrochemical analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell: Effects of anode porosity

Sentencas: Using commercial Star-CD software with the es-sofc module, Simulations are performed to obtain the current-voltage (I-V) characteristics of a fuel cell as a function of the anode porosity and the temperature distribution within the fuel cell under various operating conditions.
Titulo: Thermal stress and thermo-electrochemical analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell: Effects of anode porosity

Sentencas: The temperature field is then imported into the MARC finite element analysis (FEA) program to analyze thermal stresses induced within the cell.
Titulo: Thermal stress and thermo-electrochemical analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell: Effects of anode porosity

Sentencas: The numerical results are found to be in good agreement with the experimental data.
Titulo: Thermal stress and thermo-electrochemical analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell: Effects of anode porosity

Sentencas: It is shown that the maximum principal stress within the positive electrode-electrolyte-negative electrode (PEN) increases at a higher current and a higher temperature gradient.
Titulo: Thermal stress and thermo-electrochemical analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell: Effects of anode porosity

Sentencas: It is recommended that the temperature gradient should be limited to less than 10.6 degrees C mm(-1) to maintain the structural integrity of the PEN.
